commit 57b4055a56ff0e5376d04bea8df2080d6cf54819
Author: Josh Bailey <josh@vandervecken.com>
Date:   Sat May 9 23:54:16 2026 +0000

    Add monitor commands for keyboard injection and screen scraping
    
    New `keymatrix` command pokes the C64 keyboard matrix directly so any
    program (including direct CIA1 scanners) sees the input; releases the
    key the moment the program is observed reading the matrix rather than
    guessing a hold duration. New `screenscrape` command emits VIC-II
    state plus screen RAM, color RAM, and the active charset in one shot
    so an external app can read the display without OCR. Both are
    accessible from the text monitor and as binary-monitor opcodes
    0x74-0x77.
    
    A new Dockerfile + .dockerignore build a slim headless image for
    driving the emulator from another application over the binmon port.
    
    Run `./autogen.sh && ./configure --with-alsa && make -j` (or
    `docker build .`) after clone — autogen regenerates Makefile.in,
    mon_lex.c and mon_parse.{c,h} from the .am/.l/.y sources in this
    commit, so they are intentionally not duplicated here.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

