commit 8aeba46864461a3de5151c1e93d044997cdd5b85
Author: Josh Bailey <josh@vandervecken.com>
Date:   Mon May 11 23:56:57 2026 +0000

    binmon: add silent-checkpoint flag for byte-granular polled coverage
    
    Adds a per-checkpoint `silent` flag exposed through CHECKPOINT_SET body
    byte 9 (optional, backward-compatible — length-9 bodies leave silent=false).
    When set, the on-hit handler increments hit_count but skips the
    unsolicited CHECKPOINT_INFO event, trace prints, disassembly, and command
    execution.
    
    Motivation: polled-coverage harvesters (defmon-src installs ~45K
    stop_when_hit=false watchpoints over the code band) only need cumulative
    hit_count, which they read via checkpoint_list. Under the un-patched
    binmon, every hit emits an event; warp playback produces ~10^7 events/s,
    bottlenecking VICE itself on event emission (sweep wall 8.5 min →
    134 min) and wedging the binmon pipeline behind a multi-million-event
    queue (stop_playback etc. time out post-warp).
    
    A/B benchmark (4096 cps × 10 s warp playback): silent mode emits 0
    events, registers 440K hit_count (vs 190K loud), no command timeout.
    Same 607 distinct cps hit — coverage attribution unchanged.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

